Title : Robert Blake Yardley
Text : {{Use dmy dates|date=May 2015}}
{{Use British English|date=May 2015}}
'''Robert Blake Yardley''' (1858â€“1943)<ref>''[http://www.abps.org.uk/Awards/Roll_of_Distinguished_Philatelists/RDP_Background_20111231_LR.pdf Background notes on The Roll of Distinguished Philatelists September 2011]'', Roll of Distinguished Philatelists Trust, London, 2011. [https://www.webcitation.org/6OlHSBOTl Archived here.]</ref> was a British Barrister and [[philatelist]] who signed the [[Roll of Distinguished Philatelists]] in 1921.<ref name=abps>[http://www.abps.org.uk/Home/Who_Was_Who/index.xalter#Y Who Was Who in British Philately], [[Association of British Philatelic Societies]], 2014. Retrieved 29 April 2014. [https://www.webcitation.org/5zDx9UBpl Archived here.]</ref> He was a member of the [[Yardley of London|Yardley]] soap manufacturing family.

Yardley's worldwide collection was auctioned by H.R. Harmer over sixteen days in 1944-45.<ref name=abps/>

==Publications==
*''The Dies of the Postage Stamps of Portugal of the Reigns of Dona Maria II and Dom Pedro V''. 1907.
*''The Samoa Express Postage Stamps''. 1916.

